==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deliquiate
<hw>De*liq"ui*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>deliquia</ets> a flowing off, a gutter, <ets>deliquium</ets> a flowing down, fr. <ets>deliquare</ets>. See <er>Deliquate</er>.]</ety> <def>To melt and become liquid by absorbing water from the air; to deliquesce.</def> <rj><au>Fourcroy.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deliquiation</ent>⟦br⟧
